      Accessibility

      Accessibility Group
      Empathy Lab
      To get started, click on 'show all headings' or 'unlabelled form elements' in the nub. To test your feature alone, click the 'Test your Feature' button and click on your feature to run the tests.
      Test your Feature
      Take the HIKE below to test for accessibility!
      H — Headings and semantics
      Write semantic markup so screen readers can understand them i.e. use tags such as h2, ul, button instead of unsemantic divs.
      Show all headings
      Show all landmark roles
      I — Images and non-text content
      Images and other non-text content need textual descriptions so screen readers can announce them correctly i.e images need an alt text (alt="" if decorative), image only buttons need labels and videos need captions.
      Images without alt attributes
      Links with images that have alt=""
      K — Keyboard navigation
      Keyboard only and screen reader users cannot use the mouse. So, make your content usable with just the keyboard and manage keyboard focus.
      Links without href attributes
      Buttons built with unsemantic divs or spans
      E — Extra love: ARIA
      ARIA attributes such as aria-label, role, aria-checked convey additional info to screen readers.
      Links with href="#" and no role attribute
      Unlabeled form elements
      Show all roles
      Show basic ARIA attributes
